{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"10d5f6f7-1da1-420d-b6d6-93c52907ef7a","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. Here's the breakdown:\n\n**Framework support dropped in MSTest v3:**\n- ❌ **`netcoreapp3.1`** — not supported (EOL)\n- ❌ **`net5.0`** — not supported (EOL)\n- ✅ **`net462`** — still supported\n\nMSTest v3 requires **.NET 6+** for the .NET (Core) side.\n\n**Other migration notes:**\n1. **Package consolidation** — MSTest v3 offers a single `MSTest` meta-package, replacing the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` + `MSTest.TestAdapter` references.\n2. You'll need to update your `TargetFrameworks` to replace `net5.0` → `net6.0` (or later) and `netcoreapp3.1` → a supported TFM before upgrading.\n\n**Recommended updated TFMs:**\n```\nnet8.0;net462\n```\n(or `net6.0;net462` if you need the oldest supported .NET)\n\nWould you like me to update the project file for the migration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d3092a54-7b3c-4af4-b200-6edcc2eef807","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user's project targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. They're using MSTest v2 (2.2.10) and want to migrate to MSTest v3.\n\nMSTest v3 dropped support for older frameworks. Let me think about what I know:\n\nMSTest v3 (MSTest 3.x) has the following key changes:\n- It requires .NET 6+ or .NET Framework 4.6.2+\n- `net5.0` is NOT supported by MSTest v3 — .NET 5 is out of support\n- `netcoreapp3.1` is NOT supported by MSTest v3 — .NET Core 3.1 is out of support\n\n\n- `net462` (.NET Framework 4.6.2) should still be supported\n\nSo the user will face compatibility issues with `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` targets. Additionally, MSTest v3 consolidates the package structure — instead of maintaining separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages, they'd use a single `MSTest` meta-package or `MSTest.TestFramework` 3.x.","outputTokens":575,"requestId":"702B:3BA9A2:3AEF2B:456A2E:69F2BF9B"},"id":"063e542f-4ca7-4a30-808d-ed187a4e454d","timestamp":"2026-04-30T02:34:17.296Z","parentId":"ef4649a8-8517-4e37-b11c-6163017adcc0"}
